    <h1>Privacy Policy for Hell's Chamber</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: 5/25/2025</em></p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>SunLab Games</strong> ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you play the Hell’s Chamber VR game ("Game").</p>

    <ol>
        <li><strong>Information We Collect</strong><br />
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> We collect your email and password when you create a Unity user account to authenticate multiplayer features.</li>
                <li><strong>Gameplay Data:</strong> We collect data related to your gameplay experience to provide game functionality and improve our services.</li>
                <li><strong>Voice Chat Data:</strong> If you use in-game voice chat powered by Vivox, voice audio data is transmitted through Vivox’s servers for real-time communication. We do not record or store your voice communications.</li>
                <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We collect information about the VR hardware you use to help optimize the game.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li><strong>How We Use Your Information</strong><br />
            We use your information to:
            <ul>
                <li>Provide and maintain multiplayer and voice chat services.</li>
                <li>Authenticate your user account.</li>
                <li>Communicate with you about updates or support.</li>
                <li>Improve and personalize the gaming experience.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li><strong>Data Sharing</strong><br />
            We do not sell or rent your personal information. We share necessary data with trusted third-party service providers such as Unity Services and Vivox solely to provide the features of the Game.
        </li>

        <li><strong>Data Security</strong><br />
            We implement reasonable measures to protect your data but cannot guarantee absolute security due to the nature of the internet.
        </li>

        <li><strong>Children's Privacy</strong><br />
            The Game is not intended for children under 13 years old. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13.
        </li>

        <li><strong>Your Rights</strong><br />
            You can contact us to request access, correction, or deletion of your personal data at any time.
        </li>

        <li><strong>Compliance with Meta Quest Store</strong><br />
            This Privacy Policy complies with Meta’s Developer Policies concerning user privacy and data protection.
        </li>

        <li><strong>Changes to This Privacy Policy</strong><br />
            We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. Changes will be posted with an updated date.
        </li>

        <li><strong>Contact Us</strong><br />
            If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: <a href="mailto:sunlabgamesstudios@gmail.com">sunlabgamesstudios@gmail.com</a>
        </li>
    </ol>
</body>
